1. Launch Amazon EC2 instance (t2 small) with ubuntu image
2. Create a keypair
3. Connect to EC2 instance remortly
4. Run a command 'sudo apt update'
5. Run a command to install python 'sudo apt python3-pip'
6. Create a virtual environment 'python3 -m venv airflow_venv'
7. Active the virtual environment source airflow venv/bin/activate 
8. Install  s3fs to interact with S3 bucket using command'pip install s3fs'
9. Install apache airflow to to orchestrate the workflow 'pip install apache-airflow'
10. Start standalone Airflow environment using command 'airflow standalone '
11. Enable the port 8080 in EC2 to enable airflow
12. Connecting VS code to EC2 instance
13. Creating a DAG with name weather_dag.py

